  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Human Rights Workshop for Journalists. 4 return tickets Nairobi-Geneva, travel insurance, visa and per diem. Media21 Human Rights Workshops (HRW) intends to enhance and deepen the journalists&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99; understanding of human rights principles and protection mechanisms. Through this workshop journalists will be provided with relevant information, including human rights definitions, legal frameworks and enforcement mechanisms, and with the necessary means to detect human rights violations and address relevant bodies for their necessary actions. Under international human rights treaties, States are responsible to respect, protect and fulfill obligations including prosecuting those responsible for human rights violations. Therefore, journalists will learn how to utilize these tools to detect human rights abuses, report on actions taken by the governments and to hold abusers accountable.</narrative>
  </description>
